---
import MonarchBasicPage from "../components/MonarchBasicPage.astro";
import LegalArticle from "../components/LegalArticle.astro";

const linkClass =
	"font-semibold text-brand-black underline decoration-monarch-500/40 underline-offset-2 hover:text-monarch-500";
---

<MonarchBasicPage
	title="Legal info | Monarch"
	description="Company and legal information for Monarch, the parent company behind Monarch Modding, Operation Monarch, Monarch Software, and Monarch Hosting."
	eyebrow="Legal"
	heading="Legal info"
	lead="Who we are, where we operate, and how to reach us for legal or regulatory enquiries."
	mainClass="mx-auto mt-20 flex max-w-7xl flex-col gap-10 px-6 pb-20"
>
	<LegalArticle>
		<h2>Company overview</h2>
		<p>
			Monarch is the parent company behind the services and brands listed on this website. We build and support DayZ
			communities through custom content, live servers, software, and related digital work.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Trading name:</strong> Monarch</li>
			<li><strong>Founded:</strong> 2021</li>
			<li><strong>Active in DayZ since:</strong> 2019</li>
			<li><strong>Base location:</strong> New Hampshire, United States</li>
			<li><strong>Operating model:</strong> Remote first team with a United States base</li>
			<li><strong>Primary website:</strong> monarch-dayz.com and related Monarch group domains</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Brands and services</h2>
		<p>Monarch operates or develops the following focused brands. Each has a defined remit. Delivery standards are shared across the group.</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Monarch Modding</strong> custom weapons, gear, configs, imports, retextures, and workshop releases</li>
			<li><strong>Operation Monarch</strong> community servers, events, and player facing live worlds</li>
			<li><strong>Monarch Software</strong> panels, APIs, bots, dedi utilities, and tooling that connects game data to the web</li>
			<li><strong>Monarch Hosting</strong> infrastructure aligned with Monarch stacks and operations where offered</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			Partner hosting or infrastructure may be provided through approved partners where stated on a specific service page.
			That does not change Monarch responsibility for work we scope and deliver directly.
		</p>

		<h2>What we do</h2>
		<p>
			Monarch provides commissioned work for server owners and communities, retainer partnerships on a sprint cadence, and
			one off projects across game content, software, web development, design, media, and digital marketing. A full list of
			typical deliverables is on our <a class={linkClass} href="/work-with-us">Work with us</a> page.
		</p>

		<h2>Contact for legal enquiries</h2>
		<p>
			For privacy matters, see our <a class={linkClass} href="/privacy-policy">Privacy policy</a>. For website and service
			use, see <a class={linkClass} href="/terms-and-conditions">Terms and conditions</a>.
		</p>
		<p>
			For formal legal or regulatory correspondence, contact us through <a class={linkClass} href="/contact">Contact</a> with
			the subject line <strong>Legal enquiry</strong> or email{" "}
			<a class={linkClass} href="mailto:enquiries@monarch-dayz.com">enquiries@monarch-dayz.com</a>. We aim to acknowledge
			serious legal correspondence within a reasonable time.
		</p>

		<h2>Intellectual property</h2>
		<p>
			Unless agreed otherwise in writing for a specific project, Monarch retains ownership of pre existing tools, pipelines,
			and know how. Deliverables for clients are licensed or assigned as set out in the proposal or statement of work for
			that engagement.
		</p>
		<p>
			Third party game assets, engine constraints, and platform rules (including Bohemia and Steam Workshop policies) apply
			to modding and server work. Clients are responsible for ensuring their server and community use complies with applicable
			platform terms.
		</p>

		<h2>Disputes and payments</h2>
		<p>
			Commissioned work is governed by the terms agreed at scoping. Chargebacks are not permitted for completed work that was
			delivered as scoped. If there is a problem with a delivery, contact us first so we can resolve it directly.
		</p>
	</LegalArticle>
</MonarchBasicPage>
